(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Cloud computing delivers computing services over the internet instead of relying only on) Tj
T*
(local machines. In a textbook lesson, the first goal is to make the computing concept) Tj
T*
(clear. Students should be able to explain what Cloud Computing means, identify where it) Tj
T*
(appears in Computer Science, and describe the main purpose of the topic without relying) Tj
T*
(on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Cloud Computing is storage, servers, accessibility, and service) Tj
T*
(models. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the idea) Tj
T*
(actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or patterns) Tj
T*
(behind Cloud Computing and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In Computer) Tj
T*
(Science, success usually depends on understanding the commands, structure, and logic) Tj
T*
(that belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Cloud Computing is to connect the explanation directly to) Tj
T*
(comparing local file storage with cloud storage. That kind of system or code example) Tj
T*
(shows students how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner) Tj
T*
(should be able to state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the) Tj
T*
(question, and then apply the logical procedure with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
